     <h3> 2. Choosing Game Type</h3>

   <p>Once you have signed up, it's time to start having some fun. The first thing you want to do is figure out what kind of game you would like to play. Each game has a different chance of you winning or not and is based on the number of people entered and the amount of money for the entry fee. The types of games on fan duel are as follows:

   <h4>1. Large Multi-Entry Games</h4>- These games usual give away the most prize money to the winner but your chances of winning are highly unlikely. The entry fees on these types of games are usual about 1-5 dollars. This is like playing the lottery but it is fun because you can spend 10 bucks and enter 10 different teams if you would like too.

   <h4>2. 50/50 Games</h4> - In thfese games, you have a 50 percent chance of winning and you can bet pretty much as much as you want on these. For example the entry fee is $20 bucks, 50 percent of the participants win $40 dollars and the others earn nothing. 

   <h4>3. Head-to-Head</h4> - This on is pretty self-explanatory. Test your skills one on one against other fantasy basketball freaks

   <h4>3. Double Up</h4> - In these games, you have a chance to double your entry fee, usually around a 30-50 percent chance to double up. They also have triple up and other variations of these games.
</p>
 

   <p>Starting off, you can play in games for free, but I would reccommend doing the 50/50 games to start out and definately start off not spending more than 5 dollars on an entry fee. You should get used to the scoring and format before spending large amounts of money.

