   <h3>3. Picking Your Team</h3>

     <p> This is clearly the most important part. The tricky thing about daily fantasy basketball leagues, is the fact that they have a salary cap (60k salary cap). This can make if extremely difficult when decidng on who to start. The studs cost the most, $10,000-$12,000, and the worst players cost $3500. You can see an example below.  </p>

     <img src="http://i.imgur.com/dQjUvAn.png" class="img-rounded" style="width:450px; height:450px;" />

   

     <p>As you are picking your team, you will quickly realize how fast your money goes. Most winning teams have a combination of studs and decent players that have awesome games. A couple of strategies are as follows:
     <h4>Average Joes</h4>-This is where you do not spend any on your money of the really expensive players, and instead, you buy all quality players. This strategy is a safe bet to put up decent number and would use this when doing 50/50 games becuase you pretty much know what yo are getting, but know that the chances of getting 1st are slim.</p>
     <h4>Studs and Cruds</h4> This strategy has the highest upside, but the lowest chances of success. This is where you buy 3 or 4 really good players and hope the other, cheap players have huge games. 
     <h4>All Around</h4> This is where you get 1 or 2 studs and 1 or 2 cheap players, but the majority of the team is good quality players. This is again good to use in 50/50 games or in head-to-head, and I would say the majority of people use this strategy.

