     <h3> Things To Consider</h3>

     <h4>Injuries</h4><p>Make sure you are always up-to-date with the player's status before each game. Also, injuries can open the door for other playesr that you might be able to get really cheap.</p>

     <h4>Opponent</h4><p>You need to take into consideration what team your players are facing. They could get blown out and rest their starters(AKA someone on your team) and it could decrease their value greatly. 

     <h4>Schedule</h4>Also you need to be aware if the player's are coming off back-to-back games or a heavy raod trip or flight. These things could cause your player to perform worse than expected.

     <h4>Over Under</h4>Check the vegas stats to get an idea on if the game is expected to be high scoring, even, or a blow out. This can give you the extra edge you need to pick the right players.

